Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:03.98,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for doing that to Iroha.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.98,0:00:07.36,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to feel guilty, \Nyou shouldn't have rejected her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:08.64,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't work that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.64,0:00:12.35,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,And you know that. It's pretty mean \Nof you to put me in that position.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.35,0:00:13.24,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.89,0:00:17.21,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honestly happy Iroha feels that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.73,0:00:18.99,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,but that's not what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.61,0:00:21.66,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's really me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.14,0:00:24.49,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.98,0:00:27.46,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,the way you change everyone around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.46,0:00:29.56,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's this coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.32,0:00:32.62,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get me wrong. \NRemember what I told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.94,0:00:35.66,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the nice guy you think I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.80,0:00:42.03,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I'm complimenting you for my own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.69,0:00:49.72,Ore_Main_Top,Voice,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The train will soon arrive at \NKaihin-Makuhari. Kaihin-Makuhari.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:50.50,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the next stop is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.50,0:00:51.44,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.06,0:00:54.32,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Isshiki, I'm getting off, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.32,0:00:55.70,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Which station are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:01:00.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, my bag's really heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.39,0:01:05.13,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that might be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.48,0:01:12.86,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.86,0:01:16.97,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't need to say that now. \NYou knew it wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:20.34,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what was I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.34,0:01:22.07,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I got all excited...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.07,0:01:23.35,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That surprised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.35,0:01:25.51,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you weren't the type to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.51,0:01:27.90,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,get caught up in what's going on around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:29.48,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.90,0:01:32.11,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting more indifference.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.39,0:01:35.14,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I thought you were trying \Nto look like a love-struck fool,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.14,0:01:37.06,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,but were actually pretty clever...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.19,0:01:39.02,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Not from me. From you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.02,0:01:39.74,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.37,0:01:43.50,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'd be moved after seeing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.50,0:01:44.50,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.21,0:01:48.25,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to want the real thing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.60,0:01:51.42,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.42,0:01:53.50,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Your voice was perfectly \Naudible through the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.78,0:01:55.12,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.12,0:01:56.38,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.33,0:01:58.63,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I can't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.18,0:02:01.64,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I tried to take \Na step forward today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.64,0:02:03.44,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.89,0:02:05.56,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it get to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.56,0:02:07.39,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:10.55,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Are you taking advantage \Nof my heartbreak to hit on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.55,0:02:11.75,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I still can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:12.65,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.94,0:02:15.16,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.16,0:02:18.40,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, this is the most effective \Nway to approach Hayama-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.86,0:02:20.78,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone will sympathize with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:22.79,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,and other girls won't go near him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.79,0:02:24.03,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:25.41,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,And you know what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.62,0:02:28.12,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,It'll make people curious \Nabout the girl he rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.12,0:02:30.55,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,People will feel sorry for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:34.03,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,So this defeat is part \Nof the overall strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.87,0:02:38.29,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,To make the next phase
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.91,0:02:43.20,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,proceed... effectively...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:48.42,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:52.27,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault this \Nhappened to me, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:56.28,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the student council president \Nthing is, but the rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.61,0:02:59.52,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:10.50,Show_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(235,1)}My Teen\NRomantic\NComedy\N{\c&H8D39E0&}SNAFU\N{\c&HDCA02E&}TOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.13,0:04:38.06,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,So, um, why did you call us all here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.06,0:04:41.07,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,To confirm our objective \Nand discuss the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.07,0:04:42.17,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:44.71,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The plan currently in place \Nis, frankly, impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.71,0:04:46.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we pull it off, only a \Nsmall part will be successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.29,0:04:50.54,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,For all the ideas they threw out, \Nit'll end up being a pretty dull event.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.96,0:04:53.62,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think we should \Ndo to prevent that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:56.00,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:57.73,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The problem lies in those meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:04:59.56,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,We've pulled a lot of opinions together,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.56,0:05:02.00,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but no one has made any actual decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.43,0:05:05.99,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So let's have a proper meeting, \Nwith none of the colluding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:09.06,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll oppose, confront, and deny proposals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:10.74,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make it clear which ideas have won.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:12.87,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.64,0:05:16.12,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.60,Ore_Main,Vice,0000,0000,0000,,I think... it's better if we don't make waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.11,0:05:23.72,Ore_Main,Vice,0000,0000,0000,,And I think it'll be difficult to bring \Nup counter-proposals at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.72,0:05:25.38,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:27.02,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:33.96,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I personally don't want \Nthis event to be dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:37.02,librarycenter_05:34,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Mihama Library \N{\c&HAFCAD1&}Takasu Community Center
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:37.02,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.46,0:05:41.02,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,But personally, I think I'd \Nreally like to put on a play.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.53,0:05:44.68,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,If the audience can see both your \Nmusical performance and our play,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:47.25,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,it's a really good deal for them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.25,0:05:50.66,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,But if we separate, it would \Nweaken our synergetic effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:52.23,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,and it doubles the risk...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:52.52,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.52,0:05:54.71,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,But don't we also have a \Nbudget to consider, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.71,0:05:56.55,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all think about that together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.55,0:05:57.79,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,That's what this meeting is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:05:59.29,Ore_Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.29,0:06:00.76,Ore_Main,BG,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed, agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:01.67,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,That's the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:03.55,Ore_Main,Vice,0000,0000,0000,,Um, can I ask something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:07.14,Ore_Main,Vice,0000,0000,0000,,What's your reason for opposing \Nthe two-part event structure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.14,0:06:09.30,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not that I oppose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:13.24,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,I just think if we all share our visions, \Nwe'll bring a sense of unity to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.24,0:06:16.85,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,I think the joint event framework is a \Nmust for building a positive image, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:18.94,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it necessary to do it jointly?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:21.29,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. By doing it jointly,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.29,0:06:23.12,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,we create group synergy and \Nmake the event bigger—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:25.07,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no synergy here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:27.36,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And if we keep this up, \Nwe'll never achieve anything big.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.36,0:06:30.36,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you still hung \Nup on the form it takes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.89,0:06:32.64,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,We've reached a consensus,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:34.79,Ore_Main,Tama,0000,0000,0000,,and we've shared our ideas \Nfor the ground design.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:36.12,Ore_Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.98,0:06:36.12,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,That's the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:37.43,Ore_Main,BG,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:38.75,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.94,0:06:42.80,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I know because I had the conceited \Nidea in my head that I could do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.80,0:06:46.09,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, even though I was \Nwrong, I couldn't admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.93,0:06:49.80,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I wanted to cover \Nup my own mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:53.04,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,To do that, I used tricks and words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:55.35,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to put myself at ease by \Ngetting promises out of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:59.35,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Because when I messed up, it was easier \Nif I could blame it on someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.03,0:07:03.40,Ore_Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I get the feeling that's just \Na lack of communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:07.80,Ore_Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we take time to cool \Ndown and then discuss this again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.80,0:07:08.89,Ore_Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.80,0:07:08.89,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,That's the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.52,0:07:13.32,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to play pretend,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:15.49,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,could you do it elsewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.11,0:07:22.54,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You've been saying all kinds of \Nthings that have no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:25.37,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Is it so much fun for you \Nto pretend you're working
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.37,0:07:27.80,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,by using words you just learned \Nand mimicking a debate?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:30.31,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You use vague terms to \Nfeel like you spoke up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:31.80,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,to feel like you understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:34.10,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,but you take no action whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.69,0:07:36.72,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never move forward that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.96,0:07:39.57,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You won't create anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.57,0:07:41.10,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You won't gain anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.37,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You won't give anyone anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:44.23,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a pretender.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:46.75,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.62,0:07:51.61,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Could you refrain from wasting \Nany more of our time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.98,0:07:58.16,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, wouldn't it be more fun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:01.28,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,to let people enjoy the event twice \Nthan to force it all into one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.28,0:08:03.84,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,It would show the individuality \Nof both our schools!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.84,0:08:04.25,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:07.50,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Right. I think that sounds great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.81,0:08:10.05,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:13.35,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah... That could be cool, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.35,0:08:14.51,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:15.10,Ore_Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.10,0:08:16.61,Ore_Main,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that makes sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.61,0:08:18.30,Ore_Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.51,0:08:26.80,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you two have to say stuff like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.80,0:08:28.57,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,You totally destroyed the mood!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.10,0:08:32.08,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe anything \NI said was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.08,0:08:36.47,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,You may have been right, but you \Ncould have read the mood a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:38.30,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,There were other ways to \Nhandle that, weren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:41.67,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,If you expect him to read a \Nmood, your hope is in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.67,0:08:44.10,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Even in our club, \Nhe only reads lines of text.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.10,0:08:47.43,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but no. When you become \Na reader of my caliber,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.43,0:08:49.23,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,you can read between lines, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.23,0:08:52.51,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Also, aren't you the one \Nshe was just chewing out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:55.31,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,But Isshiki-san acknowledged \Nthat I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:08:57.69,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no reason for \Nme to be chewed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:09:01.19,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that. That's exactly \Nwhy she was chewing you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:02.72,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to what she's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.09,0:09:03.52,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.81,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Were you guys listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.81,0:09:08.88,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,I was talking to both of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.33,0:09:14.48,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Here. My treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:18.37,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.10,0:09:20.49,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.92,0:09:22.48,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:24.64,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,You've kinda changed, Hikigaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.64,0:09:27.18,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,I used to think you were totally boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.11,0:09:35.73,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,But if someone looks boring, \Nit might really be the looker's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.73,0:09:39.05,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I don't think I could \Never go out with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.05,0:09:42.30,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I didn't ask you to do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.30,0:09:43.19,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:46.19,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,As friends, I guess it might work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:47.81,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.53,0:09:51.34,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,If we have a class reunion or \Nanything, why don't you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.34,0:09:53.26,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:54.78,Ore_Main,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,I figured! That's hilarious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:56.82,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:09.88,Ore_Main,Rumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hachiman, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:12.34,Ore_Main,Rumi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need help. \NI can handle it by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.64,0:10:14.79,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe you can, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.79,0:10:15.38,Ore_Main,Rumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.61,0:10:24.85,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.85,0:10:26.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle it by myself even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:31.15,Ore_Main,Rumi,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about? That's dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.88,0:10:37.34,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So you, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.34,0:10:38.52,Ore_Main,Rumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not "you."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:40.12,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Rumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.94,0:10:43.01,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so, Rumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:46.98,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Want to be in our school's play?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:55.96,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Yuigahama-san, did you finish \Nbagging the cookies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:58.44,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I just finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.44,0:11:00.07,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to bake a cake, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:00.95,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.90,0:11:04.21,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,So don't touch these, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.21,0:11:05.07,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.07,0:11:06.47,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,That's kinda mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.32,0:11:09.06,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.06,0:11:11.30,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,We're totally in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.30,0:11:13.15,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,The scenario was well-written.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.15,0:11:14.65,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What's there to be worried about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:18.42,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,My secretary worked hard on the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:21.98,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,And, Senpai, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.73,0:11:27.08,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right! I'm gonna go \Njoin the others, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.91,0:11:30.33,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and be sure to check
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.33,0:11:32.97,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,with the vice president \Non how to time the ending!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.41,0:11:36.05,Ore_Main,Iroha,0000,0000,0000,,And take care of the cakes for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.54,0:11:37.92,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You got it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:39.84,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,President.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:38.29,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:40.92,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Good work today, Yuigahama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.92,0:13:42.43,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:49.05,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.41,0:13:50.87,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:52.51,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Your Christmas present!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:53.68,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Giving just one person a \Npaper cup would be wasteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.01,0:13:56.77,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I picked the shape, \Nand Yukinon picked the print.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.49,0:13:58.87,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I should've known.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.87,0:14:01.94,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have anything for you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.30,0:14:03.99,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.99,0:14:05.65,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a substitute for a paper cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.83,0:14:08.07,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.07,0:14:09.51,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.51,0:14:12.13,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,And for handling my request... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.70,0:14:14.96,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. You really saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.96,0:14:16.83,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It ended in success thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:19.26,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't finished your request yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.44,0:14:24.68,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,We said we'd accept your request, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.39,0:14:28.29,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah... And that just ended, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.29,0:14:30.01,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What is this, a riddle?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.26,0:14:33.51,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, maybe it is a riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.47,0:14:37.65,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.65,0:14:40.52,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's okay if you don't, Hikki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:41.41,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.41,0:14:43.57,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:45.88,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,It's still Christmas, so let's have a party!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:46.99,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:49.19,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have plans, Yukinon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.56,0:14:52.07,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,If we're having a party, \NI'll keep my schedule open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:53.80,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.80,0:14:55.85,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You're not gonna ask if I have plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.85,0:14:59.23,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Or was that a roundabout way \Nof saying I'm not invited?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:01.79,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I know you don't have any plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.09,0:15:04.79,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I want to eat some of the \Ncake you made, Yukinon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.79,0:15:06.68,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I made the cake you were eating earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.68,0:15:10.30,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If I could be given what I wished for...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.15,0:15:13.57,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If I could have what I wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:18.18,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,then I'd probably never \Nwant or wish for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:24.14,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Because the things I received and the \Nthings given to me would be fakes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.14,0:15:25.94,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,that would just disappear someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.98,0:15:29.99,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,So I think I'll keep wanting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:47.74,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what should we do about shopping \Nfor Yukinon's birthday present?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.74,0:15:49.51,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.51,0:15:51.09,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you free tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.19,0:15:55.47,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.69,0:15:58.27,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Okay, then tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.27,0:15:59.20,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:02.84,yumiko_16:00,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(425,1)}Yumiko
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.55,0:16:02.85,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's Yumiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.41,0:16:05.27,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yahello, Yumiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:06.73,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Just a sec, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.58,0:16:10.28,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what are you all doing after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:12.36,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:14.60,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care for crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.60,0:16:16.03,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,What? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.46,0:16:18.45,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see each other at school \Nagain soon, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.96,0:16:20.91,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.26,0:16:24.90,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.90,0:16:28.20,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to buy a good luck charm!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:30.43,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,I also forgot to write a wish to hang up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.43,0:16:31.72,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm gonna run back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:34.47,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, maybe I'll buy a good luck charm, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.47,0:16:36.12,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, Onii-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:38.66,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid scum-niichan! \NYou dimwit! You Hachiman!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:40.47,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Hachiman isn't an insult!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.84,0:16:43.31,Ore_Main,Komachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yukino-san, I'm gonna take off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:50.08,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.08,0:16:52.81,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid... Dimwit... Hachiman...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.81,0:16:55.53,Ore_Italics,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Yukinoshita-san's \Ndictionary of insults was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:58.02,Ore_Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,just updated for the first time in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.29,0:17:14.14,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, were you okay \Nheading in this direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:16.04,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:18.00,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it's the end of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:19.76,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought your family \Nmight be doing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:22.83,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I'm not going home this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.29,0:17:25.32,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any particular reason to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.92,0:17:29.00,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,And it won't make much difference \Nwhether I'm there or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:31.00,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Why not go, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:34.60,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,If it won't make a difference, \Nthat's easier on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.60,0:17:36.53,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't cause any problems for anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.96,0:17:40.49,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,There are people who ruin the atmosphere \Njust by existing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.49,0:17:42.29,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how you introduce yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.62,0:17:47.01,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. That's why I've always tried \Nto avoid contact with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.93,0:17:51.67,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is my stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.18,0:17:54.29,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Hikigaya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.23,0:18:00.62,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.87,0:18:27.62,kightweight,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Super Lightweight
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.98,0:18:30.96,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Kinda makes me look smart, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:35.12,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Just the idea that glasses equal \Nintelligence makes you pretty stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:37.13,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shut up, jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:41.89,bluelight_18:39,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Reduces blue light!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:41.89,compglass_18:39,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Computing Glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:45.08,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Hikigaya-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.94,0:18:48.64,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Haruno-san... and Hayato-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.79,0:18:50.65,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.94,0:18:54.48,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.79,0:18:58.24,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Yukino-chan's birthday is coming up. \NSo that's why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:19:02.85,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing you two alone together, though... \NStill getting along well, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:05.12,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,My little sister was with us at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:07.00,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,but she took off somewhere along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.57,0:19:10.00,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's unusual to see \Nyou two together, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.41,0:19:13.18,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we're here for a New Year's dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.18,0:19:16.52,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,Our parents have always been friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.82,0:19:19.38,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,They just made us come along with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.33,0:19:24.24,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,My parents are off saying \Nhello to some other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.52,0:19:26.15,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,We're waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.15,0:19:27.96,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:29.14,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:36.31,Ore_Italics,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.31,0:19:39.04,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Yukino-chan! It's your sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.04,0:19:40.57,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Can you come out right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:41.56,Ore_Italics,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:43.81,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.21,0:19:45.09,Ore_Italics,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.09,0:19:46.58,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:48.38,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.38,0:19:49.83,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Wha— Bu—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:57.06,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.06,0:19:59.09,Ore_Italics,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:01.05,Ore_Italics,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:04.43,Ore_Main,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, well, I'm... you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.39,0:20:07.64,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.57,0:20:13.21,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yukinon! Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.89,0:20:18.71,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Yuigahama-san... You're here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.10,0:20:21.35,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.35,0:20:24.95,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I was shopping with Hikki \Nand we kind of got snagged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:26.81,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I... I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:29.04,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Took you long enough, Yukino-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:32.37,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,You've got some nerve, \Nafter calling me out here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.20,0:20:37.35,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,Now, come on... It looks like \NYukino-chan hurried over...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.66,0:20:41.91,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like to \Ndrink, Yukinoshita-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.91,0:20:43.22,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have black tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.70,0:20:48.62,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,It's been ages since we all \Nhad tea together, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:49.81,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.30,0:20:52.27,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Haruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.73,0:20:56.58,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you done talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.13,0:20:57.82,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:01.53,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Hayato-kun, I'm sorry to make you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:05.07,Ore_Main,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. With everyone \Nhere, I wasn't bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.55,0:21:09.31,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Yukino, you're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.31,0:21:10.33,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:11.72,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.33,0:21:20.38,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.38,0:21:22.02,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Yukino-chan's.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.02,0:21:23.59,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.12,0:21:27.80,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know any schoolmates of \NYukino's besides Hayato-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.22,0:21:30.60,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue to be good friends to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:31.85,Ore_Main,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,We will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.99,0:21:35.08,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.08,0:21:36.10,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.14,0:21:41.13,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Yukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.44,0:21:42.51,Ore_Main,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.51,0:21:45.18,Ore_Main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,This is your birthday celebration, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.51,0:21:52.76,Ore_Main,Haruno,0000,0000,0000,,Yukino-chan, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:08.87,Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,The Thing That the\NLight in Each of Their Hands Shines On.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.43,0:24:07.80,Next_Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,#11 Hayama Hayato Always Responds to Everyone's Expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.67,0:23:40.72,Ore_Main_Top,?,0000,0000,0000,,This must be my true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.72,0:23:42.53,Ore_Main_Top,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I could never let go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.53,0:23:43.62,Ore_Main_Top,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,I just sealed it inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.62,0:23:45.38,Ore_Main_Top,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,...and pretended I didn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.38,0:23:47.95,Ore_Main_Top,?,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to be condemned by the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:49.86,Ore_Main_Top,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted someone to see \Nthat the idiotic things
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.86,0:23:51.18,Ore_Main_Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I did for others were really for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.18,0:23:53.27,Ore_Main_Top,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,In the eyes of the people looking at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.27,0:23:54.43,Ore_Main_Top,?,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I had hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.43,0:23:57.34,Ore_Main_Top,Yukino,0000,0000,0000,,...that, just maybe, someone would find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.34,0:23:59.20,Ore_Main_Top,Hayama,0000,0000,0000,,That someone would see through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.20,0:24:00.41,Ore_Main_Top,Hachi,0000,0000,0000,,Truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:04.00,Ore_Main_Top,?,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say with certainty that \Nit isn't just an empty delusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.79,0:24:07.80,Ore_Main_Top,All,0000,0000,0000,,Does something that's "real" even exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.80,0:24:09.80,Ore_Main,,0000,0000,0000,,
